The paper is about learning in large-scale systems with constraints on communication, which is a topic that falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the statistical query (SQ) model, which is a framework for learning algorithms that involves statistical queries to an oracle, and this falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper also involves analyzing the complexity of learning algorithms, which is a topic in theoretical computer science (cs.DS). The limited number of bits communicated is a constraint that involves information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper discusses the limitations of non-interactive SQ algorithms, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
